{"content_hash": "sha256:260628c085985c00baedc3d95af809b65d1cff1166dc22906f58faedacc11e69", "degraded": false, "kiq_hint": [], "language": "en", "pending_evidence_id": null, "quotable_excerpt": "RT Neel Nanda\nVery cool work! This seems a strong new tool for hypothesis generation about weird model behaviors\n\nAnthropic: New Anthropic research: Natural Language Autoencoders.\n\nModels like Claude talk in words but think in numbers. The ", "raw_path": "Information/raw/2026-05-08/x_posts.jsonl", "reliability_admiralty": "D-3", "retrieval_method": "rsshub", "retrieved_at": "2026-05-08T08:04:25+09:00", "run_date": "2026-05-08", "schema_version": "1.0", "source_title": "RT Neel Nanda", "source_type": "social", "source_url": "https://x.com/sleepinyourhat/status/2052498169930690726", "summary_for_indexing": "RT Neel Nanda\nVery cool work! This seems a strong new tool for hypothesis generation about weird model behaviors\n\nAnthropic: New Anthropic research: Natural Language Autoencoders.\n\nModels like Claude talk in words but think in numbers. The numbers—called activations—encode Claude’s thoughts, but not in a language we can read.\n\nHere, we train Claude to translate its activations into human-readable text."}
