{"content_hash": "sha256:9c4b7ff09f0d799c87bfec235ba74596198cf08e258ff1d8f66938a14c50d93f", "degraded": false, "kiq_hint": [], "language": "en", "pending_evidence_id": null, "quotable_excerpt": "RT bolna\nIndian Voice AI space just got a big update.\n\nGPT-Realtime-2 (speech-to-speech) and GPT-Realtime-Whisper (speech-to-text), @OpenAI's latest voice models, are now exclusively live on @bolna_dev. \n\nMultilingual, fluent in Indian lang", "raw_path": "Information/raw/2026-05-08/x_posts.jsonl", "reliability_admiralty": "A-3", "retrieval_method": "rsshub", "retrieved_at": "2026-05-09T07:58:46+09:00", "run_date": "2026-05-08", "schema_version": "1.0", "source_title": "RT bolna", "source_type": "social", "source_url": "https://x.com/OpenAIDevs/status/2052738904244306178", "summary_for_indexing": "RT bolna\nIndian Voice AI space just got a big update.\n\nGPT-Realtime-2 (speech-to-speech) and GPT-Realtime-Whisper (speech-to-text), @OpenAI's latest voice models, are now exclusively live on @bolna_dev. \n\nMultilingual, fluent in Indian languages, and built for voice agents that can tackle complex reasoning, perform actions, handle interruptions, and keep conversations seamless.\n\nIf you've been building voice AI for India, you'll feel right at home with these models.\n\nTry it on the Bolna dashboar"}
